Ticket late fee is a 1.5% increase of the ticket
Faculty parking can vary greatly. If tickets are paid by the next business day, the cost is often lower. This was factored into both the average and mode ticket price.

Does not include second and third offense tickets. Violation will be reduced to $7.00 if, within 30 calendar days of issuance, proof is presented to an employee at UNL Parking and Transit Services (during window hours), that a valid permit is registered to that vehicle and the vehicle was parked in an authorized location.
Failure to pay any portion of your parking tickets will result in your license plate number being placed on the impoundment list for towing. Unpaid parking tickets may also result in a student's grades or registration being held.
